I absolutely do not care about others making boxes. That is not the problem I have, it&#39;s others that try to take over the &quot;invention&quot;, almost claiming it as their own, and if you fail to properly kiss his ass, then you get publically insulted and belittled. He&#39;s done it with other people besides me, recall Joe&#39;s Box, and the Mini Box. Nothing wosre than someone that uses other people&#39;s work to make a name for himself.

 Then, all forget there is a history to radio voices, it goes back to the first invention of radio, in the beginning, it used to be called Direct Radio Voice, no one here is inventing anything new. As far as different sweep modes aka Random, as far as I can tell --useless. As far Edison--no evidence to show he made any of this stuff. 

 No one gets concept, provide the raw audio and they will talk. Doesn&#39;t matter how you make bits of speech, anything will work. 

 No matter how fancy you make the technology, it turns into a joke when people sit in a dark room and ask what color their underwear is, and insist on enhancing any fear of spirit communication.

 Yeah, I know---who cares--where&#39;s my fame and fortune!? is the onlyest qquestion. 

F-S

